body:
@guyonroche  How can I duplicate/copy worksheets on an existing workbook on my local storage? Should I access and do it inside workbook.xlsx.readFile().then()? Thank you! 

I just want to have another copy of worksheet and then just edit it. 

Or even better, if I have a template of a workbook with the worksheet on it, I'll add the worksheet to the current/selected workbook and then perform editing.

comments.body:
solved the issue, get a copy of the sheet you want to clone then create a new sheet with a standar name, then copy the model then put the real name:
```
let sheetToClone = workbook.getWorkSheet("ID TO CLONE")
let copySheet = workbook.addWorkSheet("Sheet")

copySheet.model = sheetToClone.model
copySheet.name = "THE REAL ID/NAME YOU WANT FOR THIS SHEET"

//DO STUFF HERE



return workbook.xlsx.writeFile("your_file")
